race.comment: SPIRITOFTHEWORLD (5) has gotten better with each run this time in and looks to be working up to a maiden victory. Gets in well at the weights with the 3kg claim and draws the inside marble. Ticks a few boxes for a race like this. NORTY FORTY (7) was a touch plain last time out but the two runs prior to start the career were full of merit. Can bounce right back without surprising. MISTER MIGHTY (2) wasn't disgraced in town on debut and will have derived a stack of benefit from that day at the races. In the mix. MISHANI COMRADE (1) will have come on with that first-up run now under the belt and can improve enough to feature in the finish. QUARTZOPOLIS (4) is on debut and any market confidence must be noted.
